column5: Steelheading itch ...  How is the water @ Queenston & Port D?  Thanks
no real fishing guy would try it after all this wind and rain! The fish would have retreated to deeper water!
thought so  just wanted to ask ...
great fish ...yea you never know about the weather.....ummmm so I was thinking more of Port D as unfishable.
Won't be that way for long lotta ice comming down the upper and a whole lot of mud!
Great looking fish. This pic, however had to have been taken before this weekend as the lower river was full of ice.
Full on saturday after the big wind storm pushed a bunch of ice over the boom  Sunday was fishable hardly any ice.

water has less than a foot of vis today , ice pushed out but the river is very un predictable this time of year, yesterday whirlpool was jammed with ice today it was pretty much empty i suggest coming back in july  lol

huey, take a look at the bottom right hand corner of the pic and you will see the date and time Sat morning was a freak of nature cause that rarely happens there and if alot of ice shoots down in the morning it should be gone by afternoon.  Shoot me a pm next time and I might be able to save you a trip...  cheers Streamerguy   Nice catch wiser..Don't you work lol
